Citgo Corpus Christi Refinery Shuts Process Unit on Leak

-- B y   P a u l   B u r k h a r d t
-- 
2011-05-10T18:03:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/citgo-corpus-christi-refinery-shuts-process-unit-on-leak-1-.html
Citgo Petroleum Corp. shut a process
unit at its Corpus Christi East refinery in  Texas  after a leak,
according to a local emergency planning committee notice.  At 5:45 a.m. local time, during a routine maintenance
procedure, there was a hydrocarbon leak, according to a Citgo
official. The unit was shut down and the leak is being repaired.
There were no injuries, and based on monitoring done, there was
no impact to the surrounding community, according to the
official.  The plant can process 165,000 barrels of crude a day,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Burkhardt in New York at 
 pburkhardt@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Stets at 
 dstets@bloomberg.net . 